review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2020
review.title: I gave this product 5 stars for the service not the product
review.review: When I received this product it looked amazing. The packaging was nice, it arrived quicker than we expected, and the overall presentation of the product was just what we had hoped for. However, it was dead when it arrived so I charged it for a couple of hours and when I turned it on it worked for 30 seconds, then the top screen went black, the bottom went black with and error code coming across the screeen stating to shut off the console and restart or contact nintendo support. I restarted it with the same issue three times and then I messaged the seller to make them aware that I was going to call nintendo to get to the root of the issue. When I was on the call with Nintendo we foudn that this product was not new as advertized and had the wrong programming it was not compatible with that console. I let the seller know what I had found out and they were quick to resolve the issue and apoligized perfusely for the mistake. I do not fault them for this we are all human everyone makes mistakes. We are just happy we were able to return the product without any issues and that everyone on all sides of this were extremely helpful including JMS Holdings, Nintendo Support, and Amazon Customer Service. We purchased a nintendo switch from Best Buy uptown after we received our refund from this product. I do not wish for anyone to avoid buying from this seller they werewonderful when it came down to having an issue with a product...I only wish to inform or remind those purchasing electronics to always charge the product and to try it out upon recieving it so if there is an issue theres no question as to what party is responsible only to how to get it resolved without conflict. Very thankful for all customer service representatives especially during the holidays.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on August 10, 2021
review.title: It's good for a game but awful for a pokemon game
review.review: This specific seller's product is good; Though I'd personally recommend that if your considering getting this game because it's a pokemon game and, for that matter, the newest game of the series, I'd say that you should at least consider getting a different pokemon game instead. This one has barely any content and it feels like a massive cop-out in terms of world building and, like I said, the sheer amount of content. The entire world in the game just feels empty aside from useless (short-lasting) power-ups you find laying around literally everywhere. Theres no side quests, there's barely any main quest, and on that note, the main story in the game is incredibly hard to follow, at certain points the game just stops directly telling you where to go and just expects you to find your own way. Not saying you couldn't possibly enjoy the game, but just keep in mind that just because a lot of the other, more famous pokemon games might be old, their still much better than this one.

review.title: It supports old DS games.
review.review: What I like? Large screen, fun and easy to use interface (if you blow on the mic in the menu while hovered over an icon, the icon will spin), Backwards compatibility with old DS games (thank you for letting me play Pokemon Platinum again, and overall it's just a damn good handheld system, no surprise coming from Nintendo.What I don't like. The memory card you get with the game is fairly small so if you're going for digital downloads you'll only fit one game on it. Another thing I don't like is how it doesn't have a GameBoy game slot on the bottom like the old DS but I understand that that was never in the cards for the 3DS so I'm not counting that as a negative really just more of a "I wish it were there".Other than that its a damn good system that let me be a kid again by letting me play the games I used to play under by bed sheets at night.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2021
review.title: Poor QC and horrible for you switch OLED
review.review: Other than looking really cool and being an official Nintendo product let’s get straight into why you should avoid this product.1.) Nintendo has always done well in terms of fit and finish, this is an absolute exception. Stitching seams for the white fabric are all over the place. And, the case seems 5% too big.2.) no dedicated joystick cutouts makes this case destroy your joycons especially if you have rubber joystick caps. Once you zip up the case, the case will put a lot of pressure on top of the joystick making it pressed down the whole time. This will not make your joycons last long.3.) the stand is actually pretty good but I would rather have it face the other way. The switch won’t stay up if you use the other side.4.) for its price and no hard shell, value for money is pretty low.Everyone has different uses for a case, some like it because it looks cool and they have the whole “set” while others need it for actual protection. If you’re interested in protecting your switch this case by Nintendo is definitely NOT the one to go for.
product.title: Nintendo Switch Carrying Case & Screen Protector - Switch

review.title: Cheaply made
review.review: For the price, this is junk. The zippers are low quality and get stuck around the corners. The case also has little structure and is flexible so any force/pressure applied would be borne by the Switch inside; there are better cases that are hard and have nicer zippers for the same price or less.The screen protectors are just thin plastic (wouldn't really protect against anything but fingerprints on the actual screen, though they'd still appear on the plastic protector); assuming you can install them without bubbles/dust it would provide minor protection but very minor.

review.title: Minimal, Affordable, Gorgeous case.
review.review: So many reviewers on this aren’t even purchasers. One guy even claimed it doesn’t hold games. This case is minimal but it does have room for 5 games and something small as shown in one of my photos. This case also features a built in stand which is even more stable than the stand on the new OLED switch.The color is great if you have one of the new OLED switches. The materials feel good and well constructed. The zipper is nice but unbranded. The case itself does not have any form fitting for the switch, it is flat. It’s just enough to keep the switch safe. I have a third party case which is more protective but it is very bulky. You have to decide what is best.I did not use the screen protectors. It came with 2 of them. They seemed like normal screen protectors.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on September 4, 2021
review.title: Like Stardew Valley, but cuter
review.review: In this game, you play as a soldier sent from the Capital to protect a village against monster attacks. You learn your ancestor has a farm of their own, and move into the house there. The story develops as you continue to assist the village and your fellow soldiers with their tasks, giving you access to new areas, items, and spells.This feels like Stardew Valley (closest comparison I can make), only far more fun to play, with more proper RPG elements. I tried Stardew Valley and quit a few hours in, but I binged this one on release day way past midnight. The art style is adorable, the characters are cute, and the humor is spot-on. The combat is simple enough for anyone to pick it up, but also requires enough attention that you can't just button mash. Elite Enemies are non-aggressive so they won't flatten your butt when you encounter them in a starting area- but give you a goal to get strong enough to slay them down the road. The combat also lets you pick styles of combat: Ranged, Melee, or Magic. To use your Active abilities, you need to strike enemies multiple times to restore uses of your ability dots. I like the variety, and the attacks and dodges feel rewarding. Danger areas are shown of monster attacks, and once you learn the timings of them, you can effectively dodge even head-on attacks. Money can be made in this game from simple farming to selling drops you get from monsters. It doesn't force you down one specific path for money.. (Though I would recommend hoarding until you buy weapon/armor upgrades you want- The grind to upgrade equipment is very slow, probably due to the relatively limited amount of equipment items in the game)Now for the criticism. Of course, it's not PERFECT. Nothing really is. If I had to criticize, I'd ask for a run button or better fast travel- Fast Travel exists to certain hubs, but the "checkpoint" system is where I had minor grievances. You can fast travel TO a checkpoint, but not FROM it. Meaning sometimes, you have to run across several fields and loading screens to get back to a hub. It's annoying due to the fact that time passes super quickly in the game, and a jog from a checkpoint back to the main village can easily cost you a couple of in-game hours, which is critical, as most shops only run from 7 am to 7 pm. So if you lose 4 hours, that's 1/3 of your day gone. I feel like the game should also pause when you're in your inventory or quest log- it's a bit of a hassle to worry about time while I'm reading on what I need to do on a quest. Also, as I mentioned earlier- the grind can be quite a pain. For example, you may have to kill 30+ orcs for a SINGLE weapon upgrade.Bottom line, this game is worth every penny I paid, and I'm going to be putting tons of hours into it. The majority of the hours will be ignoring the game world being in danger because I'm too busy working on my farm.
product.title: Sponsored Ad - Kitaria Fables - Nintendo Switch

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on September 3, 2021
review.title: Fun casual action RPG, with crafting and farming added in
review.review: This fun action RPG has you controlling a sword-wielding cat as you progress on your adventure.The game reminds me of a combination of Cat Quest and Harvest Moon; as it adds some farming and crafting elements to the main action RPG plot.The game does have a decent amount of dialogue, and this combined with the often time-consuming quests makes it take a while to advance, but we have mostly had fun and enjoyed the pace.The only frustrating thing so far has been the map system, and general navigation.The map is so zoomed out that it is not very helpful at all in figuring out where you have to go, so it becomes basically trial and error.If you're willing to just explore, and don't mind occasionally having no idea where to go next, then perhaps this won't bother you as much.Overall this seems like a fun game so far, and the cooperative two player gameplay has allowed the kids and adults to enjoy playing together. 3.5 / 5

review.title: Pleasantly Surprised!
review.review: I know the switch is near the end of its life cycle and just now getting one. I had been hesitant for a long time. I viewed the switch as gimmicky and made for children. After actually playing it and seeing what's available, I might have to take back what I've said about it. However, I am a pc gamer primarily. By no means it it going to achieve great graphics, but as a mobile gaming system that you can dock to a tv, its pretty great. The biggest jaw drop I have had so far is how they got Doom Eternal to run at all on the switch. I play that on pc a lot. Yes I can tell the difference, but in handheld mode and be able to take Doom Eternal anywhere I go, is simply amazing! I don't care how much reviewers down the graphics. The fact that its on there, stable 30fps and contains the entire game without massive problems is highly amazing to me. There are so many games that I did not expect to be on the switch and the fact I can play those games that I have on my pc and play them anywhere, regardless of downplayed graphics, is mind blowing.Even if they make a new switch this yr or next, its worth getting. I always purchase mid life or later because of defects anyway. So, I have plenty of time to play this system.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 16, 2021
review.title: I enjoyed it
review.review: I never played the original version of Skyward Sword so this was a whole new adventure for me. Over all I enjoyed it a lot. The temples were fun though a little too linear at times. It had my favorite features of Zelda games where you gradually collect unique items that allow you to do more things throughout the game (some more useful than others) but in this one there wasn’t a lot of back tracking to use these new items in places I had already been which I usually actually like to do. There wasn’t enough side quests or villager interaction. I enjoyed playing it both handheld and motion controls though my lazy ass preferred handheld. Both ways had some hiccups but nothing to ruin the experience.The biggest complaint that I have is that one of the big bosses that was the most annoying and wonky to fight was one that you have to fight three separate times…It’s a good game that’s worth the play but not top three material.
product.title: The Legend of Zelda: Skyward Sword HD - Nintendo Switch

review.title: Great used device.Highly recommend.
review.review: Excellent product.I was worried since I purchased a used product.The product arrived smudged and a bit dirty, but it was ok. I cleaned the device and it looked good as new.The internals seem to be fine as I have used the device a few times in the past month and it works.Battery seems to hold just fine.I have purchased game cartridges and downloaded games.Both work just fine.The controllers work great, and mine to not sway to a si gle direction like other Joy Cons, that I have read.The cradle works great and plugs easily into all of my television sets. I highly recommend and you'll be happy.I only use the device for a few hours a month so I wouldn't say that I'm a heavy gamer. Very casual so a used unit fit my needs.Very impressed and quite happy.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on August 5, 2021
review.title: Budget option, but pretty!
review.review: Just put this on today. Like a lot of generic skins, this lacks any strategic cuts around curved edges, which means you will inevitably get tiny wrinkles. I saw that from the product pictures, so I was willing to live with it, but it still docks a star. I really like the finish: matte with a textured grippy feel. Hopefully it holds up. Printing is decent but nothing spectacular. Looks fine from a distance which is all I really cared about, since I mostly play docked on the couch.BTW, application is a million times easier and more precise if you remove all the small scrap cutouts and large outer scraps first, then carefully place the skin with strips of release paper. Look up the Korean brand Pop Skin on youtube and copy how that guy does it. Genius.

review.title: Works Well
review.review: There is always install error to account for. Applying any screen protector takes some technique. With that said, this works very well. I have used the same brand on my Google Pixel 3 phone and it always worked well. Clean the screen well before applying it, but do not go overboard and saturate the screen. If the screen has bubbles you can carefully lift the edge up and then place the glass back down to get the screen to naturally push the air out.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 16, 2021
review.title: 10/10 Golden Bananas!
review.review: Banana Mania exudes joy and charm. It is a love letter to the little lovable monkeys and their fans. SEGA did an excellent job redoing the graphics in the adorable art style that started with Banana Blitz on Wii and lovely musical remixes of original tunes.Some things have been changed, including the exclusion of lives, which I was initially negative about. After playing it, feel like this design decision was not done haphazardly and is completely justified. The bananas function as collectibles that give you points in the in-game shop, so does meeting different challenge requirements, which you can achieve naturally or by checking them and going for the gold. These points add a lot of replay value and make collecting them feel worthwhile. I know I wound up really liking playing the main game or party games, wanting to take a break and use my new points to unlock things in the points shop. The costume items are cute and do feel worth it, but the heavy hitters are the plethora of playable characters you can unlock as well as the creative new modes that are new to this game, like golden banana mode where you collect all bananas in a stage and dark banana mode where you avoid all bananas in a stage.There’s so many things to unlock, this feels like a very complete package, and considering the very reasonable pricing, this is an excellent value, and even would be at full price.The game’s cute visuals and music keeps a game that can be very challenging feeling very light and happy, and like you want to come back for more.If you like feeling like you are learning and improving, this is a game for you. You can see yourself get better and master stages, once you do, you can get even more creative and try to find unlikely shortcuts. This game is really a physics puzzle with lots of action and quick thinking.I have played the original games and most of the games following it. I understand that some retro fans are disappointed this game isn’t exactly like those excellent originals, and it isn’t, but that’s okay! I’m really loving Banana Mania and learning the slight differences in it is fun. I think this game is good enough to stand on its own.Super Monkey Ball Banana Mania is a joyful and cheerful experience that makes me feel happy, and I’m thankful for that.10/10 Golden Bananas! I highly recommend it, friends!

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 8, 2021
review.title: FAR FROM THE ORIGINALS!!
review.review: If you have ever played Super Monkey Ball before in your life then do not buy this game. It is a massive downgrade from the originals - physics are changed, cutscenes are replaced, and overall speed is greatly reduced to name a few. Many of the levels feel as if they were not tested thoroughly as the new features make it very difficult to either build up enough speed or to control the map well enough to drop into goals. Not only that they've literally added a "mark as complete" option for every level in the pause screen, it makes absolutely no sense. How do you take the challenge out of Monkey Ball? I didn't think that was possible.If you have NEVER played a Super Monkey Ball game and thus have nothing to compare it to then this game may be alright for you. I suggest playing the originals to get the full experience as they are far superior to this easy mode cash grab from Sega. The original game had Dole brand bananas in it. This one couldn't even get the Chiquita sticker. That alone should be enough for you to make an informed decision on the two.
product.title: Sponsored Ad - Super Monkey Ball Banana Mania: Anniversary Launch Edition - Nintendo Switch

review.title: Party games are a disappointment

Every single party game, and I mean all of them, play terribly. There was absolutely no effort placed into these party games to make them look or play like the originals. Instead, they feel like cheap rip-offs that have been tacked on.If all you want is to replay the main game, then I can at least say that that portion of the game does play pretty well and had some thought and care put into it. But the party games are an absolute joke.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 21, 2021
review.title: Not a PERFECT fit, but still good
review.review: I lined the screen protector up with the bottom right corner and got it perfect. The right and bottom are fully covered, but the top and left have a slight gap.Other than that, this product has worked very well. My old switch scratched from my nails, this hasn't scratched at all.I read the other reviews and many had problems with the dust wipes and alcohol wipes. My switch was new and I handled both of the wipes very carefully, so my screen underneath is in perfect condition.I applied one to my sibling's switch and it has a bubble on a part of the non-screen area. This is because I had to pull it up to better align it. On my own switch I did not have this problem because I did not pull it back up, so I suggest taking your time and doing it as steady as possible. The product come with two screen protectors, so if you only have one switch you can retry or save it as a replacement if the current one ever gets scratched.The touch sensitivity and ability to fit in the dock are not affected, by what I have seen.I recommend this, but am just a bit annoyed at how it was so close to fitting perfectly.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 3, 2021
review.title: Initial setup an issue? Test other controllers
review.review: I purchased this switch up for Pokemon shiny hunting, and had some issues with getting a controller to connect. As someone has already said in a previous review- switch pro controllers made by Power A will not connect to this device. If you are not sure if your controller is a Power A, there should be a sticker label that has the manufacturer name at the top. If this is the case for you, you may want to try a wired connection to a different controller. PS4 was a very easy set up. You can either watch their video on YouTube- or simply wire everything together, hold the PS4 and share buttons, and it will connect instantly. Then, simply follow the instructions for their other video explaining how to set up shiny hunting. I hope this helps anyone looking to get started! Best wishes.

review.title: Works Well
review.review: Mainly used it for auto shiny hunting. Got like 1 shiny every day or 2. 3 days for unlucky ones.There is one thing that didn't work right, it was the macro recorder, or the instruction is unclear on how to use it. There is no one else online other than the basic video that is not too clear on how to use it. I tried resetting the recording but it's still stuck on the down button. Not enough info on how to reset that.Other than the macro recording not working right everything else works perfectly as intended.Pokemon swsh egg hatching time shown by the light on the drive, up to 4 lights. Least you should go is 2 down after seeing the 2nd light.5000 steps: 2 down from second light7000 steps 1 down or leave exactly at 2 lightsMore?: probably exactly at 2 lights.You don't have to hatch one at a time, you can let a few in the party at the same time, so save time and hatch more. With this it's approximately 1 box per hour.

Simply plug it into your PS5 and it will work with PS5 & PS4 games. You can use it on any game but if the game uses twin analog stick for movements it wont work too well. I def recommend this as a starter arcade stick because its made of mostly plastic and already I'm kinda worried if I go too hard on it during a session I'll end up snapping off the joystick. If I end up using it a lot I will upgrade to a more sturdy (expensive) model.

review.review: I dont take the time to review products often, but I cant stress enough to STAY AWAY from this company when purchasing any type of electronics. I ordered the PS4 bundle with the spiderman game and 2nd controller. First off, the 2nd controller didnt come with the original bundle. I had to waste time going back and forth with them to finally send me the 2nd controller, which came about a week after the original bundle. Fast forward to Christmas day. My son finally gets to open his gift, only to find out that each game we tried, gets the error message that I attached in the photo. The system clearly didnt work and we decided to return it. The return process was going smoothly, until I noticed I was missing 157.00 from my return. I reached out to get an explanation and they claimed that it worked and they were taking 157.00 for a no longer needed fee. If it worked as promised from the start, there wouldve been no need for me to return it in the first place. In sumarry, im getting my lawyer involved to recoup my full refund!! JUST DO YOURSELF A FAVOR, AVOID THIS COMPANY!

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 16, 2021
review.title: Fun and follows the series
review.review: I'm not really into fighting games, but it made me think of the DBZ games so I went for it. I am a fan of Demon Slayer and was excited to see a game for it. I am impressed that all the original English VAs from the anime are in this game. The visuals are stunning and the fighting is unique depending on the character. The game follows the anime/manga all the way through to the Mugen Train arc.I took off a star because: Tanjiro has the same type of responses when talking to people in towns. The roster is fairly small for a fighting game and you have to go through story mode in order to unlock more characters. (You could also grind away in multi-player to unlock characters but it's way faster to do it through story mode). I hope more variety is added character wise later on. Once you finish story mode there's not much replay value unless you enjoy online multi-player. Another thing that was a little annoying: most of this game is cutscene heavy. I understand it is for retelling the entire story, but I felt like I spent most of my time watching vs playing.IF YOU ARE A STREAMER..... be warned there are stream restrictions in place, so make sure you look into it before attempting to stream.I do recommend this game if you're a fan of the series, I did throughly enjoy playing the game.

review.review_data: Reviewed in Canada on October 18, 2021
review.title: Not worth the full $90 price in my opinion…But…Depends on what your looking for out of this…
review.review: Visuals look amazing!!! But…I find the story gameplay to be way too linear…Kinda reminds me of how linear FFXIII was…As in the map…Your just walking in straight lines to get to your point of destination with fights in between…Just the way the story gameplay is executed…Feels bland…And not that interesting…The storyline itself I like…As I’m a fan of demon slayer…Just not the story gameplay…Also…It’s more watching the story I find…Rather than more playing…It’s a short one with 8 Chapters…Well 9…If you count the prologue…Combat is the best part of the game…It’s fun…Fast paced…Yet simple…Although…I find it to be just a tad bit too simplistic…And repetitive…Which…Simple gameplay mechanics isn’t necessarily a bad thing…It still can be fun…I just think it would’ve been better…And more fun to execute combos with a mixture of different button combinations…Rather than just pressing the square button most of the time…As far as game modes…There’s just only 2 modes…Story…And Versus…Wish there were more single player modes…Like a survival mode…Or endless mode…Having the online play is great…And all…But…When you don’t play much online…Like me…It leaves the game with little to do…And gets boring quickly…Character roster is small…A total of 18 characters…Kinda disappointing…It’s also disappointing to see that the bottom characters are just some of the same characters…Just with different outfits…Waste of character space in my opinion…All those same character spots could have been added with completely different characters…But…I read online that there will be DLC characters coming…So…The roster could get better in time…Overall…The game is alright…I just think it’s lacking content with characters…And game modes…Kinda makes me feel like I should have waited for a price drop on this…Don’t think it’s worth the full price of $90 in my opinion for what little amount of content you get…If you just wanna get it because your a fan of demon slayer…Like me…Or anime fighting in general…Then…Go for it…Or if your just gonna play it for the online portion only…And don’t care about the lack of single player/game modes…Then…Yeah…Go for it…But…If you don’t play much online…Like me…And were looking for more content out of this in terms of single player/game modes…Then…I would wait for a price drop…3/5stars…

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2021
review.title: Buggy Money Grab
review.review: This game should be a textbook example of why no one should get exclusive rights to IP. Beyond steadily increasing prices on the game, the entire thing is to push you into Ultimate Team, where you’ll need to spend significant money to stay competitive. The servers are crap, and the game is rife with bugs (ie counters don’t work cuz the QB runs into shifting linemen). There are limited time events to get free players but the game crashes and server outages will handicap your ability to take advantage of them. If you complain about the poor quality of their service, they will copy paste a detailed cop out blaming your internet connection, even if you provide screenshots showing it’s on their end. Buy the game used from someone who has given up on this 💩, and don’t buy anything in game if you NEED a fix
product.title: Madden NFL 22 - PlayStation 5

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 9, 2021
review.title: Shame
review.review: Returned to Madden after 17 years. (Yes, seriously.) What was once a great franchise is now a shell of itself with a game engine called Frostbite that is long in the tooth. I found gameplay to be super awkward. Running was near impossible even on Rookie mode. Interceptions by the CPU felt very forced at times. At times it felt impossible to defend against the pass. Commentating was exhausting. What happened to fun gameplay? I guess ultimate team ruined this once great franchise.Visually it was beautiful on the PS5 and my new 4K TV. But fun it certainly was not. Hopefully the NFL will allow for competition or Madden will actually start to make an effort on gameplay once again. Shame.
product.title: Madden NFL 22 - PlayStation 5

Thanks Amazon for great Madden22!Your friendJeffrey Jade Robert Schultheis

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 5, 2021
review.title: Returned game
review.review: Last bought madden in 18. Usually just play franchise mode so no great need to get it every year. I thought I'd get it now for ps5... It has to be just as good, if not better... right? I was blown away by how unplayable this is. The bugs are so bad you can barely call it a football game. Gameplay is so far away from reality it's like fortnite made a football game. Some examples:- You thought you won a regular season franchise game? Nope—bug says you lost 30-0 and all your stats from the game are deleted.- You thought you were tackled to the ground? Nope—bug says you can get back up and run again.- You thought throwing to an open receiver in the endzone was a good idea? Nope—bug says it might hit off of him, travel 5 yards to a defender, have him catch it, and boom the camera angle suddenly changes to midfield (despite everyone still being near the end zone).- You need to punt the ball? Nope, just kick it into the end zone and you might get a touchdown.- You thought you're running zone coverage on defense? Nope—bug says one of your defenders might just stop somewhere in the field to leave the receiver wide open. Same goes for your receiver running routes because they might just randomly stop for a second.Plenty of more bugs out there. You can watch all of these bugs on youtube as well. Why wait for patches to a game EA might not even fix? I'd only recommend buying it so you can return it to send a message to EA.
product.title: Madden NFL 22 - PlayStation 5

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 22, 2021
review.title: Works with PC! No extra software needed.
review.review: Always been a big fan of playstation controllers as opposed to the xbox controller, so when sony released this work of art I had to try it. Now I don't play on console. I play on PC. Which makes this controller versatile. If you do have a PS5, obviously this will work with it. If you want to use this with PC, this also works with PC. It's pretty simple to hook it up to your PC (given your PC has bluetooth.) This is how you connect it to your pc.Turn bluetooth on (on pc)Hold the create/share button WHILE holding the PS button on the controller until the controller starts blinking.On the pc, click on add bluetooth devices.Select "bluetooth"The pc will begin searching for bluetooth devices.Once the controller is found "wireless controller" will show up as a selection.Select wireless controller and it will connect. The controller should light up dark blue.Launch Steam. The controller should now show up as a light blue.Now open steam and go into steam settings.Click on controller, then go to "general controller settings" select "Playstation configuration support".At this point steam knows you have a controller connected and it should appear under "detected controllers"Now launch your games! If you don't ever turn bluetooth off, then the next time you turn your pc on it should connect right away. If not you just press the PS button which turns the controller on and will connect to your pc automatically, (unless you have a another device connected etc)With steam you can change the colors of the contoller also, so in my case when I turn on my controller it goes from dark blue to light blue and finally green.This by far is one of the greatest controllers I have held in my hands. My hands are normal sized, and this doesn't feel too big or heavy. It feels premium and the seemless conection between my PC and controller make me recommend this to everyone who wants to play games with a controller on their pc with NO extra software!
product.title: PlayStation DualSense Wireless Controller – Midnight Black

review.title: Wonderful controller, questionable QC.
review.review: The PlayStation Dualsense (DS5) controller has several features that the previous generation didn't, but I fear that quality control may be an issue. I was lucky enough to receive a perfectly functioning DS5 with my PlayStation 5, the controller model is the newer of the two current variants.When shopping for a second controller, I purchased one brand new from Amazon in midnight black. When it arrived, this model is the older of the two variants. The left thumbstick was creaking in various spots and felt like it had areas of resistance in the range of motion. Amazon was kind enough to send a replacement that arrived the following day. The replacement is also the older variant of the DS5 controller, however, this controller is perfect.Long story short, if you purchase one brand new from Amazon and it creaks, squeaks, or doesn't feel as it should, request a replacement. I feel that PlayStation needs to focus more on their quality instead of quantity, and consumers deserve to receive an acceptable product with every purchase, especially when these next-gen controllers cost as much as they do.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on September 15, 2021
review.title: Bad Writing and Wokeness, other than that, pretty great!
review.review: This game looks great, feels responsive, and improves on the movement from the first game. A lot of the traversal things you needed to unlock in the first game are available from the get go, like being able to do a high jump running start, etc.The new powers of electricity and invisibility are fantastic and you will use them a lot. The stealth gameplay is a lot better in this game.I like a lot of the characters in this game like Miles friend Ganke, but some not so much. I also enjoyed a lot of the story elements and the passing of the torch.My biggest/Only problems with this game are the writing and some "woke" stuff.The main antagonist is very horribly written in the latter half and without spoiling anything, has a lot to do with miles. I will include a spoilers section below on my issues with the story. Not only her, but also some other things as well.Also, going back to the woke part in the game. Early in the game, theres a rally. There, you literally meet a deaf person and right after that 2 l3sbians, like it is really forced. Some people will say whats wrong with that, nothing inherently except the latter part, but it is clearly pushed in your face and because they are in later parts of the game as well.Then they got the B-L-M wall in the game and they force you to interact with it because after you finish all the phone app missions, they put the suit they make you right underneath it and it has like 2 different camera pans just showing the wall like "Yeah, that's right, this is good and we believe it and we need you to know and see and were so good".Also the Danika stuff was so cringe and I am glad you're able to just disable her permanently, sadly though not for the construction site missions that makes absolutely no sense why she is involved, like she's some master reporter hacker on the case.Overall, the combat and movement were improved from the first game, had some great characters like Miles, Ganke, prowler, cool missions and side stuff, etc. Really its just the writing/woke that makes this a 3/5 for me.----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------SPOILERS BELOW: WRITING ISSUES:The writing in the 2nd half with tinkerer was awful. Her not telling Miles about anything, then when he figures it out, she gets weird that he doesn't want to tell her anything, when she was lying and hiding the whole time and he figured it out without her confiding in him. Then her intentions and trust are just stupid for no reason, then she literally bombs like 1000 cars and possibly kills hundreds of people and just an overall awful person, then "sacrifices" herself in the end as if she is this amazing person. Also, why in the world were Miles closest friends/family like 10 ft away from the reactor in the end, they were literally supposed to run away like an hour before that and they all just ran back there in 2 secs???
product.title: Marvel's Spider-Man: Miles Morales Ultimate Launch Edition – PlayStation 5

review.review_data: Reviewed in Canada on October 16, 2021
review.title: New to the serie and love it!
review.review: I want to be clear. I have never played a naruto or demon slayer game before. Im more of the "jrpg turn base" type of guy and im already in love with this game. Story mode is fun. Lots of collectibles to unlock such as profile pictures and costumes. Voice acting is good. Ranked multiplayer is where you'll spend most of your time I think because the story mode is around 15 hours (40+ if you want to unlock everything).Dont be fooled by people who say its only 30 fps and is unnaceptable on ps5. I can tell you I play PC games at 100+ fps and this game is a solid smooth 30fps that honestly feel like 50 fps. There is already a 60 fps patch announced by the dev and coming soon.Pick it up!!

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on May 19, 2021
review.title: Condition not even close to advertised!
review.review: First let's start off with the conditions it arrived in which is poor when it was advertised as good. The console still functions as intended but there are scratches and scuffs all over it.The controller is no better and rather much worse. As there is notable wear and such as a chunk missing out of one of the analog sticks.The sellers description specifically said no writing in the product. But there is writing on both the power supply and the controller. It also said they would provide the hdmi cable but instead I was given a AV cable that isn't even for this model of Xbox.And lastly shipping. While it did arrive in the may 13th and the 21st time window. For the amount of time it took for them too even ship my item would atleast make you hope that there is some protection like bubble wrapping the snot out of it so it doesn't get damaged. Well... wishful thinking cause the only thing that would protect this contents of this box are your hopes and dreams and ya best hope the ups man don't kick that too.The games are fine. Both copies seem too be in good condition. No major scratches. Both are clearly just picked up from a used game store. Tomb raider even still has sticker residue on it. But I can't complain there. Even if I cared about that kinda thing it pales in comparison to the other stuff I've mentioned and it's easily resolved with goo goneToo sum it up. I am extremely unimpressed by the products condition. And will do my best too magic eraser the name of the powersupply. And the controller will soon see a landfill as basicly any movement and it disconnects. I'd save your money and try and find one some where else.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on February 16, 2021
review.title: Careful what generation you use this supply for.
review.review: So to note that the original xbox 360 that sold from 2005 to roughly 2010. Those consoles used, on average 160 Watts. And shipped with a 200 watt power supply brick.The Xbox S (or slim), used on average 70 to 90 Watts.This brick is rated for 125 Watts. So sticking this supply to an older gen Xbox will likely result in a failure or catastrophic failure of the supply.Another difference is this supply has the a standard C13 cord with a hot, neutral, and ground pins.The old Xbox 360 brick only had A hot and neutral pin.Other noted difference the power light on the OEM brick when plugged in to the power it shows orange, when the Xbox E turns on it goes green.This brick shows red when plugged in and goes green when the Xbox is turned on.Disclaimer: I have not extensively used this power brick yet, just used it to power up a Xbox 360 E COD Special Edition console that I refurb'ed.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 20, 2021
review.title: Fast But Weird Setup
review.review: I was really wanting this from the time I bought my Xbox Series X and finally got it. 1 terabyte is just not enough storage, and frankly, this additional terabyte hardly slakes my thirst for more storage. Games are getting so big, now, I may still have to add USB storage.This device is fast. Load times are noticeably faster. But the set up is weird. The instructions come in the way of a simple graphical sheet that seems to indicate you just plug it in, so I did what most people would do and powered down my unit and plugged this in. After powering up, I transferred some of my games and apps from the internal drive to this without problem.However, when I went to play a game or start an app that I had transferred to the Seagate, I got an error that it would not run. After some sleuthing online, I found someone in a forum relating that he was told to leave the power on while plugging in the device. So I powered down the Xbox, took the Seagate out, powered up the Xbox, and while powered up, crossed my fingers and plugged in the Seagate.All was right in the world and it's been working fine ever since.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 21, 2021
review.title: Not great, not terrible
review.review: Oculus Quest 2 is really great if your intention is just to play Beat Saber all day. But the reality is that practically speaking, it's a lower resolution and lower tier VR experience. Facebook's own Horizon Workspaces doesn't work very well on the Quest 2, because it has low resolution and trying to focus your eyes on your computer screen in VR Is not very fun. Immersed (another VR workspace app) is okay, and low enough latency for decent work in VR but the resolution of the Quest 2 will still bite you.Apps like YouTube VR are okay, because the screen is practically at the optimized FOV convergence point. But the reality is that the display is so low resolution that 360 videos kinda don't look great on the display anyway. It's really a shame.A different head strap is mandatory. This hurts a TON after wearing it for any extended period of time. Impressively bad head strap. Will leave red marks on your face.Finally, the biggest thing I haven't mentioned is that the device itself runs Android, and it's a pretty low powered android device. Unfortunately, this means that apps like YouTube VR can lag and stutter, which really sucks more in VR than any other device. In VR, lag and stuttering means that your view suddenly freezes, which immediately creates motion sickness. Not great.But it's an okay first experience for VR. It's a great Beat Saber machine. For anything other than Beat Saber, you're probably better off waiting for the Quest 3 or getting a different VR headset with higher resolution displays and better FOV lenses.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on February 15, 2021
review.title: This seller rocks!
review.review: When my old 360 broke, I figured I was going to have to settle for a beat-up used model that likely received more damage in the shipping process. I stumbled across this seller and this xbox 360 for a price that beat everyone else I had found, and I got a little suspicious that for that price it must be beat up. I decided to take a chance because of their 5-star rating... Well, they have earned that status!This was better than I could have asked for. Not only did it arrive a week early, but it was diligently packed in such a way that I couldn't imagine anything being damaged, even if a shipper dropped it on to pavement. Bubble wrap, newspaper, etc. Very well done. The cables looked brand new and were neatly twist-tied, and the console itself appeared new too! Everything works great. These people know what they're doing and they clearly take great pride in their work. I'm so excited this worked so well for me and I will be buying any future "older" gaming products I need from them.

review.title: Fast But Weird Setup
review.review: I was really wanting this from the time I bought my Xbox Series X and finally got it. 1 terabyte is just not enough storage, and frankly, this additional terabyte hardly slakes my thirst for more storage. Games are getting so big, now, I may still have to add USB storage.This device is fast. Load times are noticeably faster. But the set up is weird. The instructions come in the way of a simple graphical sheet that seems to indicate you just plug it in, so I did what most people would do and powered down my unit and plugged this in. After powering up, I transferred some of my games and apps from the internal drive to this without problem.However, when I went to play a game or start an app that I had transferred to the Seagate, I got an error that it would not run. After some sleuthing online, I found someone in a forum relating that he was told to leave the power on while plugging in the device. So I powered down the Xbox, took the Seagate out, powered up the Xbox, and while powered up, crossed my fingers and plugged in the Seagate.All was right in the world and it's been working fine ever since.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on May 19, 2021
review.title: Condition not even close to advertised!
review.review: First let's start off with the conditions it arrived in which is poor when it was advertised as good. The console still functions as intended but there are scratches and scuffs all over it.The controller is no better and rather much worse. As there is notable wear and such as a chunk missing out of one of the analog sticks.The sellers description specifically said no writing in the product. But there is writing on both the power supply and the controller. It also said they would provide the hdmi cable but instead I was given a AV cable that isn't even for this model of Xbox.And lastly shipping. While it did arrive in the may 13th and the 21st time window. For the amount of time it took for them too even ship my item would atleast make you hope that there is some protection like bubble wrapping the snot out of it so it doesn't get damaged. Well... wishful thinking cause the only thing that would protect this contents of this box are your hopes and dreams and ya best hope the ups man don't kick that too.The games are fine. Both copies seem too be in good condition. No major scratches. Both are clearly just picked up from a used game store. Tomb raider even still has sticker residue on it. But I can't complain there. Even if I cared about that kinda thing it pales in comparison to the other stuff I've mentioned and it's easily resolved with goo goneToo sum it up. I am extremely unimpressed by the products condition. And will do my best too magic eraser the name of the powersupply. And the controller will soon see a landfill as basicly any movement and it disconnects. I'd save your money and try and find one some where else.

review.title: Best Budget option for next gen gaming
review.review: Very affordable next gen system came with everything you need for budget high powered gaming system. Comes with the console much smaller than the x box one much easier to store and fits very easily on a shelf or desk, a free HDMI chord, a power chord and a controller which feels much durable than previous x box box controllers. The console does have a cooling fan on top which makes for longer gameplay without overheating and the only downside to the console which isn’t really a downside if you hate going in public is the system doesn’t have a insert slot to put physical copies of your gaming disk. Overall a great gaming system with great performance at a lower cost. You may need to buy more storage for this system if you’re a true gamer like me for hours and hours of gaming fun :)

review.title: Not worth the price
review.review: The out of the box experience isn't great - ear pads are uncomfortable out of the gate and take a couple of weeks to really break in. Mic monitoring is horrid at default settings, and while it can be corrected you have to connect to a computer and run updates - not what you're looking for in a piece of console hardware.Once the ear cups are broken in and you've done the updates, these will be acceptable for a while, with only a few annoyances like random de-syncing... and then the headband will just randomly break one day while you're wearing the headset. I got about 8 months of use from mine before it broke, but it sounds like a lot of people have had even worse luck with durability.Not at all what I expected from Turtle Beach at this price point...

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 19, 2021
review.title: The wifi situation
review.review: Okay so I can see where people are saying you can't connect. I've experienced it too and I was super bummed. This is what I did. Don't bother with the xbox app. Power cycle the xbox. Turn it back on and press "add a wireless connection" you are not going to refresh the list of networks and put password. You're going to again look for "add wireless connection" option and manually type out the SSID then the password and it should work. This is what I did. I hope it helps you if you're out there freaking out. Another option I would try is temporary having your wifi password public just for this setup. I noticed my xbox connected to my Hotspot so that should work too. I'm not sure why these xbox have these wifi issues so I'm going to rate it low. Why give us such a scare.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 20, 2021
review.title: Fast But Weird Setup
review.review: I was really wanting this from the time I bought my Xbox Series X and finally got it. 1 terabyte is just not enough storage, and frankly, this additional terabyte hardly slakes my thirst for more storage. Games are getting so big, now, I may still have to add USB storage.This device is fast. Load times are noticeably faster. But the set up is weird. The instructions come in the way of a simple graphical sheet that seems to indicate you just plug it in, so I did what most people would do and powered down my unit and plugged this in. After powering up, I transferred some of my games and apps from the internal drive to this without problem.However, when I went to play a game or start an app that I had transferred to the Seagate, I got an error that it would not run. After some sleuthing online, I found someone in a forum relating that he was told to leave the power on while plugging in the device. So I powered down the Xbox, took the Seagate out, powered up the Xbox, and while powered up, crossed my fingers and plugged in the Seagate.All was right in the world and it's been working fine ever since.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 21, 2021
review.title: The console is just OK
review.review: I have had my Series X for a year now and feel I can give a full review finally. The console is just mediocre, the graphics are fine the games are awesome in fact I think Gamepass Ultimate is the best value in gaming right now, I just wish Microsoft had a console that matched it.The audio from the console itself is just silly, unless your TV/Monitor has built in speakers or audio out then you will need to use a HDMI audio extractor, an official wireless headset, or wired headphones connected to the controller, also no bluetooth connections so most modern headsets, and sound systems are useless with this console.The wifi can be very finicky and drops a lot, no other wifi device I have loses connection as much as this console so I have started to use a wired connection.Only 1 USB port in the front is lackluster.This feels like a $300 console not a $500 one.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 12, 2021
review.title: Awesome value, great for small hands, *won't* be keeping
review.review: First, I have to commend Victrix on the really, really aggressive pricing for this controller. As of writing (Oct. 2021), you get trigger locks, four (or two) paddles, two faceplates, solid build quality, and fine adjustments via app for just $100, which is WILD in a market dominated by $180-200 options or even higher! $100 is a statement, for sure. I really hope this gives "big controller" a run for its money. I would love to see folks like Razer forced to actually look at their designs instead of using the same uncomfortable paddles since 2017. Heck, maybe it'll push Microsoft to add a third set of triggers (Razer M1/M2 style) to an Elite Series 3!Anyway, I love almost everything about this controller. Buttons are clicky and very responsive, I love having five different positions I could lock the triggers to, and the shape feels very ergonomic in a way some elite controllers don't quite nail. I even grew to love the purple/white aesthetic. It's a looker and it's clear a lot of thought and care was put into this pad.Honestly, for the value proposition and feature set, you can't beat the Gambit. That said, **extremely nerdy nitpicks incoming**This won't unseat my Elite Series 2 as my daily driver, for a few reasons.1) I love the idea of the back paddles being flush with the grips, but in practice, it ends up feeling a bit "cramped" back there. Maybe this won't be an issue for smaller hands, but keeping my middle finger and ring finger positioned on both paddles means the fingers are basically pressed together, which isn't a natural, comfortable grip.2) Having to "squeeze" my fingers to actuate those back buttons moves the controller slightly every time. In fast-paced FPS games, I felt this was throwing off my aim a bit. The Elite Series 2 doesn't "jitter" when you use the paddles, probably because they're a bit detached from the unit itself.3) Maybe it's an issue with my particular unit, but the purple silicone "Match Silencer" faceplate is just different enough sized from the white plastic plate to cause issues. We're probably talking nanometers, but it's enough where my left analog stick can't reach its 100% full tilt in a few places. My movement felt a bit slow in-game, so I checked out the Victrix Control Hub app for calibration, and I couldn't complete the "rotate your analog sticks" test because it wasn't *quite* seeing the full, complete rotational movement.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 15, 2021
review.title: Overall good gameplay but bugs and confussion abound
review.review: UPDATE: There are three things a seasoned Far Cry Player likes to do: Scout a target to see where all the soldiers and alarms are , be able to quickly change weapons as needed, understand the current objective.I have put this game away for the time being because so many of the missions are ill defined and enemies keep coming even when you turn off all the alarms. Down one helicopter using all your ammo and another shows up. Shoot everything in sight, allies even show up as if you are about to capture the area, then more soldiers materialize out of thin air. So much for scouting and planning!! It is unclear whether you are to accomplish a small objective and run away or capture the area. I would rather play when it is fixed, if ever, I say that because after the last update yet another big problem...The weapons wheel is malfunctioning.At first I thought my controller had gone bad, but I added a brand new wired controller and the same thing happened. First the wheel is hard to generate and may blink off. Then you are frozen on your current weapon and can't move the wheel. Next the weapon isn't really chosen and the wheel stays up, blocking whatever is shooting at you. You have to click the right control button to make it go away. But you still have the issue of not changing the weapon. So you might be fighting a helicopter with a hand gun. It makes the game unplayable.Old review below.....This could be a glitch in the xbox one version but there are a lot of retrieval and inventory issues.Could not kick in the boards on the bunker to get my first supplies. After capturing the first fort and spending a lot of time looking for and finding the armory key, I arrived at the door only to find the key missing from inventory. I went back to make sure I had taken it and i had.Once you leave the small island you've fled to and return to the main there are other issues. Checkpoints are easy to claim, but if you enjoy taking out alarm systems on forts without being detected, then removing the guards to claim the area, that doesn't seem to work anymore. Enemies keep coming, often appearing where you just shot one. Sooner or later you get killed or run out of supplies. I don't think the game is supposed to do this. It isn't fun if it is. I tried shooting every vehicle that arrived as well and nothing changed. Wait a few moments and the enemies appear again.The next issue has to do with picking up an item and also taking to people using the x command. Standing in exactly the right spot to generate the command gets old. Trying to pick up gear ten times in a row or simply get someones attention is not fun and you begin to wonder if you are really supposed to talk to them.There may be a global fix for this that they can apply, but it doesn't affect all objects and people.

review.title: Excellent so far
review.review: I've been playing Far Cry 6 on the Xbox One for several days now, ever since the day it came out. The disk works perfectly with zero glitches, unusual for a huge game. Far Cry 6 looks like it will have a lot of playability since you have lots of stuff to do and lots of ways to do it.I can't complain about the game mechanics. Everything seems to have been thought through well. As is usual with the Far Cry series, you start with a small map and gradually expand your activities to bigger maps. And as you would expect from a Far Cry game, there are lots of quirky characters and you spend time capturing bases, crafting, and defeating evil characters.Every one of the games in the Far Cry series has improved on the previous game (although probably the original Far Cry was more fun than Far Cry 2 for most players). This game has every indication of being the best in the series and one of the greatest games to date.

review.title: It works
review.review: This gets 5 stars because it functions as it should… but there are some things to note for the cheap people like me.1. It comes with a couple Duracell batteries which is nice but the device itself does not have an inner battery than can be charged via usb-c.2. When plugged in (to my pc running windows 10) it works perfectly fine but there is always a Microsoft Visual C++ Runtime Error that pops up and I haven’t troubleshooted it yet because it doesn’t seem to affect the functionality of the controller.3. It does not work with my cheap wireless dongle that plugs into the pc. Given that the cheap dongle I have was an absolute nightmare to get working with 360 controllers in the first place, this didn’t surprise me but is worth noting if you don’t have Bluetooth and want to be wireless.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 15, 2021
review.title: Overall good gameplay but bugs and confussion abound
review.review: UPDATE: There are three things a seasoned Far Cry Player likes to do: Scout a target to see where all the soldiers and alarms are , be able to quickly change weapons as needed, understand the current objective.I have put this game away for the time being because so many of the missions are ill defined and enemies keep coming even when you turn off all the alarms. Down one helicopter using all your ammo and another shows up. Shoot everything in sight, allies even show up as if you are about to capture the area, then more soldiers materialize out of thin air. So much for scouting and planning!! It is unclear whether you are to accomplish a small objective and run away or capture the area. I would rather play when it is fixed, if ever, I say that because after the last update yet another big problem...The weapons wheel is malfunctioning.At first I thought my controller had gone bad, but I added a brand new wired controller and the same thing happened. First the wheel is hard to generate and may blink off. Then you are frozen on your current weapon and can't move the wheel. Next the weapon isn't really chosen and the wheel stays up, blocking whatever is shooting at you. You have to click the right control button to make it go away. But you still have the issue of not changing the weapon. So you might be fighting a helicopter with a hand gun. It makes the game unplayable.Old review below.....This could be a glitch in the xbox one version but there are a lot of retrieval and inventory issues.Could not kick in the boards on the bunker to get my first supplies. After capturing the first fort and spending a lot of time looking for and finding the armory key, I arrived at the door only to find the key missing from inventory. I went back to make sure I had taken it and i had.Once you leave the small island you've fled to and return to the main there are other issues. Checkpoints are easy to claim, but if you enjoy taking out alarm systems on forts without being detected, then removing the guards to claim the area, that doesn't seem to work anymore. Enemies keep coming, often appearing where you just shot one. Sooner or later you get killed or run out of supplies. I don't think the game is supposed to do this. It isn't fun if it is. I tried shooting every vehicle that arrived as well and nothing changed. Wait a few moments and the enemies appear again.The next issue has to do with picking up an item and also taking to people using the x command. Standing in exactly the right spot to generate the command gets old. Trying to pick up gear ten times in a row or simply get someones attention is not fun and you begin to wonder if you are really supposed to talk to them.There may be a global fix for this that they can apply, but it doesn't affect all objects and people.
product.title: Far Cry 6 Xbox Series X S, Xbox One Standard Edition

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 10, 2021
review.title: Excellent so far
review.review: I've been playing Far Cry 6 on the Xbox One for several days now, ever since the day it came out. The disk works perfectly with zero glitches, unusual for a huge game. Far Cry 6 looks like it will have a lot of playability since you have lots of stuff to do and lots of ways to do it.I can't complain about the game mechanics. Everything seems to have been thought through well. As is usual with the Far Cry series, you start with a small map and gradually expand your activities to bigger maps. And as you would expect from a Far Cry game, there are lots of quirky characters and you spend time capturing bases, crafting, and defeating evil characters.Every one of the games in the Far Cry series has improved on the previous game (although probably the original Far Cry was more fun than Far Cry 2 for most players). This game has every indication of being the best in the series and one of the greatest games to date.

review.title: Not worth the price
review.review: The out of the box experience isn't great - ear pads are uncomfortable out of the gate and take a couple of weeks to really break in. Mic monitoring is horrid at default settings, and while it can be corrected you have to connect to a computer and run updates - not what you're looking for in a piece of console hardware.Once the ear cups are broken in and you've done the updates, these will be acceptable for a while, with only a few annoyances like random de-syncing... and then the headband will just randomly break one day while you're wearing the headset. I got about 8 months of use from mine before it broke, but it sounds like a lot of people have had even worse luck with durability.Not at all what I expected from Turtle Beach at this price point...

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 20, 2021
review.title: Fast But Weird Setup
review.review: I was really wanting this from the time I bought my Xbox Series X and finally got it. 1 terabyte is just not enough storage, and frankly, this additional terabyte hardly slakes my thirst for more storage. Games are getting so big, now, I may still have to add USB storage.This device is fast. Load times are noticeably faster. But the set up is weird. The instructions come in the way of a simple graphical sheet that seems to indicate you just plug it in, so I did what most people would do and powered down my unit and plugged this in. After powering up, I transferred some of my games and apps from the internal drive to this without problem.However, when I went to play a game or start an app that I had transferred to the Seagate, I got an error that it would not run. After some sleuthing online, I found someone in a forum relating that he was told to leave the power on while plugging in the device. So I powered down the Xbox, took the Seagate out, powered up the Xbox, and while powered up, crossed my fingers and plugged in the Seagate.All was right in the world and it's been working fine ever since.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 21, 2021
review.title: The product is awesome backed by solid Customer Service
review.review: When I first got the batteries and the charger, I plugged them in and charged them till all 4 lights were green. It didn't take long, even with USB charging so I guess they'd been charged before shipping. Always nice!I put one of the batteries in the controller and it wouldn't turn on. I tried another battery and it worked so I put the bad battery in the charger and it showed green as if it was charged.I tried it again... still nothing.I tried the other batteries and found the other 3 batteries worked fine.I was a little miffed and contacted the seller and they responded within the hour. They asked if shipping out another battery would be OK or did I want to replace the item or send it back for a refund. Always nice to have options!I took a chance and asked them to ship another battery to me and surprisingly it was at my door a couple of days later... and it worked! The seller even followed up to make sure everything was OK.For such a cheap item (in the scheme of things) I was very impressed by the Customer Service. They obviously stand behind this product... andfor good reason!I've usually bought chargers that provide a door for the XBox controller to charge through and rest in a cradle but I'd just bought a Series X and couldn't find one where the door fitted on the new controllers. I took a chance on these batteries and I can say for the two or three months I've been using them, they seem pretty solid, especially for the price!I'm not on the Xbox every day but when I use it, I use it for prolonged periods and the batteries just seem to keep running. They've far outlasted any batteries I've bought before.Great product and definitely worth a buy, backed by great Customer Service!

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 21, 2021
review.title: The console is just OK
review.review: I have had my Series X for a year now and feel I can give a full review finally. The console is just mediocre, the graphics are fine the games are awesome in fact I think Gamepass Ultimate is the best value in gaming right now, I just wish Microsoft had a console that matched it.The audio from the console itself is just silly, unless your TV/Monitor has built in speakers or audio out then you will need to use a HDMI audio extractor, an official wireless headset, or wired headphones connected to the controller, also no bluetooth connections so most modern headsets, and sound systems are useless with this console.The wifi can be very finicky and drops a lot, no other wifi device I have loses connection as much as this console so I have started to use a wired connection.Only 1 USB port in the front is lackluster.This feels like a $300 console not a $500 one.

review.review: The Headset looks great and sounds great when its not distorted and garbled. It's fine for an hour or so then it will randomly start distorting the audio and will persist till you power the headset off and back on. Razer claims this is a known issue with the new Xbox Series X but it falls short of what MS actually has to say about the issue. The only known issue for the integrated wireless xbox headsets is the audio cut out that requires you to wiggle the thumb sticks. While this headset does not suffer from this issue, I find Razers claims to be FALSE or missleading. I returned the first one and the replacement was even worse with this issue. If you are okay with powering the headset off every couple of hours then this may be the headset for you but I personally would have to recommend to pass on this one till Razer get this issue fixed.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 4, 2021
review.title: Great headset, insane battery life, but there's some hoops to jump through...
review.review: Ok, decided to invest in a legit headset to game on my Xbox Series S with.Ordered a "used" one from a third party seller on Amazon saving myself about $100 by doing so.I get my unit, and despite Amazon saying this was indeed for Series S/X, it did not initially work.I had to hook the base station up to my computer and update the firmware on it first, download a Dolby app on my Series S, and then it would let me set it up as my headset.Quite a bit of steps to jump through, and not a single bit of documentation to walk you through it.So getting set up was a much bigger pain than it should have been.But now that it's set up?It's a beast.The headset sounds amazing.The battery life made it through almost 21 hours of a buddy's 24 hour stream that we were doing.It's very comfortable also.If you are buying this for your Series S/X, and don't mind doing some google searching to get set up, it's an amazing headset.If you are not inclined or do not have a home computer, you might want to give this a pass.
product.title: ASTRO Gaming A50 Wireless Headset + Base Station Gen 4 - Compatible with Xbox Series X|S, Xbox One, PC, Mac - Black/Gold

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on October 3, 2021
review.title: Died after 5 months of average to low use
review.review: This headset died after 5 months of use.Prior to completely dying, it was fairly consistently having issues the whole time.More often then not the Xbox wasn't seeing the microphone.After unplugging and plugging back in the charging base the Xbox would then recognize the microphone.The current problem is related to charging, and holding a charge.The headset will no longer charge on the base.Not sure if it is the headset or the base that is the issue.I have been fighting the charging issue as well periodically during the 5 months of use.Either way this is a very expensive headset and hasn't lived up to the price tag. When it did work it sounded good, but I don't believe it sounded any better then the Turtle Beach headset that I had prior to this.I would recommend you purchase a different product.
product.title: ASTRO Gaming A50 Wireless Headset + Base Station Gen 4 - Compatible with Xbox Series X|S, Xbox One, PC, Mac - Black/Gold

review.review: This controller was absolutely amazing at first. The batteries last forever compared to AAs or a rechargeable pack. The extra buttons can be mapped so you don't have to take your fingers off the sticks giving you a great advantage in FPS games.However after less than 4 months the left stick is starting to drift making it a liability online. Microsoft support wants me to mail it in and it will either be repaired or replaced after 2 weeks.As nice as it is I would rather have kept the controller that came with the console now. This controller is too pricey to not be able play for that long. I gave my other controller to a friend after theirs was damaged so it's the only one I have.Update: I chatted with MS rep and they pretty much confirmed that the stick drift is caused by adjusting the tension on the sticks. So even though it's a feature you should never adjust it lol.

review.title: IF YOU ARE GETTING 600 MB/S WRITE SPEEDS READ THIS!!
review.review: I see some questions and reviews about getting 600Mb/s in tests on windows. This happened to me too. I did some digging and found out that you can change a setting to increase it to around 1900 Mb/s (likely the real world max). My first test transferred files at 350 Mb/s from my internal 970 evo to the X5 (the speed test was 600, real world was 350) and now it's transferring at 1.4 Gb/sWARNING!!!!! IF YOU DO THIS YOU MUST MANUALLY EJECT YOUR DRIVE EVERY TIME OR RISK DATA LOSS!!!WARNING!!!!! IF YOU DO THIS YOU MUST MANUALLY EJECT YOUR DRIVE EVERY TIME OR RISK DATA LOSS!!!To eject a drive on windows, look in the system tray on the bottom right hand corner of the screen and find the "safely remove hardware" icon. Click it and select the X5HOW TO INCREASE WRITE SPEED:Go to device managerexpand "disk drives" menuright click the X5go to policies tabcheck "better performance"check "enable write caching on the device"do NOT check "turn off write cache buffer"click okay and the device will reconnect.Enjoy 1900 Mb/sREMEMBER THAT YOU MUST EJECT THE DRIVE MANUALLY IF YOU SELECT THIS OPTION!!!!REMEMBER THAT YOU MUST EJECT THE DRIVE MANUALLY IF YOU SELECT THIS OPTION!!!!

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on September 17, 2021
review.title: Advertised speeds with TB3/TB4
review.review: Your browser does not support HTML5 video. Strangely, this thing gets better write speeds then my internal Sabrent Rocker Q4 Gene nvme drive. The Sabrent wins in reads bit even when plugged into a TB4 elements hub, I get full speeds as my ASRock Nuc only has 1 TB4 port.I'm currently usíng this as my performance tier drive for windows storage spaces with 2 14TB WD 7200RPM in a simple virtual disk (software RAID0). This has to be configured via PowerShell and is not supported by Microsoft. Essentially anything written to the 25.7TB drive is written to the X5, then the X5 writes the data to the spinning drives in the background. This gets me 1.6GB/s write speeds in bursts, then drop down to 600/500MB/s. It will get a bit slower if you fare copying enough data to fill the X5. Meaning that since I got the 500GB model, speed will start to slow down when transferring over 500GB of data which is rare. You can do this by creating different tiers. Google "Storage spaces ssd cached drive" to learn how to set it up this way. If you attempt to do this via the GUI you will just blindly be throwing this in and would be a complete waste.
product.title: Sponsored Ad - Samsung X5 Portable SSD - 1TB - Thunderbolt 3 External SSD (MU-PB1T0B/AM) Gray/Red

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on September 15, 2021
review.title: Just as fast or faster than the built-in drive!
review.review: I absolutely LOVE this drive. For not a whole lot of money, its Thunderbolt connection gives me speeds just as fast as the built-in SSD on my mid-2020 iMac. It's perfect for holding my Steam library, collection of virtual machines, emulator ROMs, and other things that I don't want NAS latency for.

review.review: I needed to buy this to replace my iMac's failed Fusion drive. It performs BETTER than using the internal Fusion drive did. I only wish it had been more clear about already coming with a Thunderbolt cable. I bought one thinking that it didn't, but could have saved the expense since this came with one. Speaking of expense, this is definitely a pricey item. But the performance is exceptional! It can run hot, however, depending on use.

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on September 8, 2021
review.title: Fast, Nice Design and Construction But Prone to Thermal Throttling
review.review: This is a very well made external SSD and for many tasks will perform flawlessly, resulting in fast transfers or 2K video editing, etc. The main problem with this device (and it's common / not specific to Samsung) is that after a few mintues of continuous data transfer or other demanding task, the NVMe drive inside will start to rapidly heat up. When it gets to a certain temperature, the device automatically throttles down to prevent damage to the drive or internal components, then after a few minutes of low use or idle time, it will return to a state where it can deliver top speeds. The best I've seen were over 2200 MB/s write and 2500 MB/s read, but more typically you'll see something like 1200 MB/s write, because of the problem described above. Still faster than a Gen 2 USB drive but a pretty big drop regardless.So if you're looking to use this for highend video editing (feeding raw footage off the drive), you probably will want to look elsewhere. If you just want a really fast backup drive or a working drive for your Photoshop projects or the like, it's great. The main limits will be encountered by video profressionals and scientific computing professionals.
